File: MTN branding seen at an event. BackpagePix/Samuel Shivambu JOHANNESBURG - One of Africa's biggest mobile network operators, MTN has been accused of indirectly supporting an Iranian terrorist campaign. A lawsuit filed in the US further alleges that MTN's support of the terrorists led to Americans being injured and killed in Iraq. READ: It happens in all war zones: Analyst on MTN terrorism scandal Chinese technology company ZTE has also been implicated in the lawsuit. More than 50 Americans claim MTN and ZTE did business with the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps. The lawsuit highlights that the business was done knowing that the transactions would help finance the Iranian group's terror campaign in Iraq. A similar complaint was filed in 2019 by more than 150 Americans, who claim the company paid the Taliban not to attack its mobile phone towers in Afghanistan.